    "description": "<p><strong>Simple Tools for Real World Regeneration</strong></p><p><br></p><h2>About</h2><p><br></p><p>Green Goods puts simple tools in the hands of communities doing regenerative work — planting trees, building solar hubs, cleaning up waste sites, and teaching the next generation.</p><p><br></p><p>Gardeners document their work with photos and field data using an offline-first mobile app that works even without internet. Operators verify submissions, and every approved action creates a permanent, verifiable record of real-world impact.</p><p><br></p><h2>GOODS Token</h2><p><br></p><p>GOODS tokens tie it all together: stake to join a garden community, signal which work matters most, and share in yield generated by the protocol. Every ETH contributed to this project backs the GOODS token and funds the communities doing the work.</p><p><br></p><p>Four domains. Twenty-two actions. One protocol for proving that the work got done.</p>",
